It turns out that the fastest implementation is _mulspsp3 (which is the same as the one used in sparse.py) is fastest.
However, great improvement is shown in sparse*vec. I will just take a single example as I have earlier written that new algorithm is O(nnz) asymptotically in any case.
m =
[1, 2, 0, 0, 0, 0]
[0, 3, 0, 4, 0, 0]
[0, 0, 5, 6, 7, 0]
[0, 0, 0, 0, 0, 8]
and equivalent csr= [[ZZ(1), ZZ(2), ZZ(3), ZZ(4), ZZ(5), ZZ(6), ZZ(7), ZZ(8)], [0, 1, 1, 3, 2, 3, 4, 5], [0, 2, 4, 7, 8], [4, 6]]
n = Matrix([[ZZ(4)], [ZZ(7)], [ZZ(12)], [ZZ(14)], [ZZ(17)], [ZZ(2)]]) (vector)
